ol.li: accept(): Kernel allocates lowest available FD (Slot 4), creates struct socket.

close(4):
task_struct->files->fdt[4] is set to NULL.
struct file refcount decremented.
If refcount == 0, struct socket destruction begins (FIN/RST).
EMFILE: If accept() is called but all 1024 slots are non-NULL, kernel returns -1 and sets errno to EMFILE.

g.title: Result of close(4). Slot returned to bitmap allocator.
ulimit -n reached. Next accept() returns EMFILE.
